{{Use Australian English|date=February 2018}} {{Use dmy dates|date=February 2018}} {{Infobox Australian place | type = town | name = Colinroobie | state = nsw | image = Colinroobie Rural Fire Service Shed.JPG | caption = Rural Fire Service shed | lga = Narrandera Shire | postcode = 2700 | coordinates = {{coord|34|32|19|S|146|35|36|E|display=inline,title}} | pop = | est = | elevation= 291 | maxtemp = | mintemp = | rainfall = | county = [[Cooper County, New South Wales|Cooper]] | fedgov = [[Division of Riverina|Riverina]] | stategov = [[Electoral district of Cootamundra|Cootamundra]] | dist1 = 579 | location1= Sydney | dist2 = 79 | location2= [[Griffith, New South Wales|Griffith]] | dist3 = 28 | location3= Barellan | dist4 = 24 | location4= [[Narrandera]] <ref>[http://www.travelmate.com.au/MapMaker/MapMaker.asp Travelmate] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070324192800/http://www.travelmate.com.au/MapMaker/Mapmaker.asp |date=24 March 2007 }}</ref> }} '''Colinroobie''' is a rural community in the central part of the [[Riverina]] in southern New South Wales, Australia. Previously referred to as ''Bents&nbsp;Hill'' its name was changed in January 2005.<ref>{{NSW GNR|id=JPIOlMrXMa|title=Colinroobie|accessdate=}}</ref>
It is situated by road, about {{convert|24|km|mi}} north of [[Narrandera, New South Wales|Narrandera]] and {{convert|28|km|mi}} south of [[Barellan, New South Wales|Barellan]].
Colinroobie Post Office opened on 5&nbsp;November 1895 and closed in 1952.<ref name = "PostOffice">{{Citation| last = Premier Postal History | title = Post Office List | url = https://www.premierpostal.com/cgi-bin/wsProd.sh/Viewpocdwrapper.p?SortBy=NSW&country= | accessdate = 2009-06-11}}</ref>
