{{Infobox album | name = Material Action 2 N.A.M. | type = studio | artist = [[Merzbow]] | cover = MerzbowMaterialAction2NAMCover.jpeg | alt = | released = {{Start date|1983}} | recorded = September‚ÄìOctober 1982 at Junktion Music Work, Tokyo | venue = | studio = | genre = [[Noise music|Noise]] | length = {{Duration|m=40|s=59}} | label = Chaos | producer = Masami Akita | prev_title = [[Lowest Music 2]] | prev_year = 1982 | next_title = [[Erotrograph]] | next_year = 1983 }}
'''''Material Action 2 N.A.M.''''' is an album by the [[Japan]]ese [[noise music|noise]] group [[Merzbow]]. It was the first non-[[Compact Cassette|cassette]] Merzbow release. The "2" in the title refers to ''[[Yantra Material Action]]'', which was intended as the first Merzbow [[Gramophone record|LP]]. Chaos was distributed by Eastern Works, which is sometimes listed as the label.<ref name="merzbook">{{cite book |title=Merzbook: The Pleasuredome of Noise |last=Woodward |first=Brett |year=1999 |publisher=[[Extreme Records|Extreme]] |page=94 |isbn=0-646-38326-4}}</ref> The album was later included in the ''[[Merzbox#Material Action 2 N.A.M|Merzbox]]''.
On June 8, 2016, the album was reissued as a replica LP pressed on colored vinyl by Menstrualrecordings.
