{{Infobox airport | name = Sadiq Abubakar III International Airport | nativename = | image = | IATA = SKO | ICAO = DNSO | type = Public | owner-oper = [[Federal Airports Authority of Nigeria]] (FAAN) | city-served = [[Sokoto]], [[Nigeria]] | location = | elevation-f = 1010 | elevation-m = | coordinates = {{coord|12|54|58|N|5|12|25|E|type:airport_region:NG}} | pushpin_map = Nigeria | pushpin_label_position = | pushpin_label = '''SKO''' | pushpin_map_alt = | pushpin_mapsize = | pushpin_image = | pushpin_map_caption = Location of the airport in Nigeria | website = | metric-rwy = y | r1-number = 08/26 | r1-length-f = | r1-length-m = 3000 | r1-surface = Asphalt | footnotes = Sources: FAAN<ref name=FAAN>[http://www.faannigeria.org/index.php/airports/major-domestic-airports/sokoto FAAN - Sokoto Airport]</ref> WAS<ref name=WAD>{{WAD|DNSO|source=[[DAFIF]]}}</ref> GCM<ref name=GCM>{{GCM|SKO}}</ref> Google Maps<ref>[https://www.google.com/maps/@12.9163845,5.2057374,3800m/data=!3m1!1e3 Google Maps - Sokoto]</ref> }}
'''Sadiq Abubakar III International Airport'''<ref name=WAD /> or '''Sultan Saddik Abubakar Airport'''<ref name=FAAN /> {{airport codes|SKO|DNSO}} is an airport serving [[Sokoto]], the capital of the [[Sokoto State]] in [[Nigeria]]. Arik Air does daily operation from Abuja and Med-View Airlines does flights to Jeddah during Hajj using a 747.
The Sokoto [[VOR-DME]] (Ident: '''SOK''') and [[non-directional beacon]] (Ident: '''SK''') are located on the field.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ourairports.com/navaids/SOK/Sokoto_VOR-DME_NG/#lat=12.921099662780762,lon=5.229310035705566,zoom=10,type=Satellite|title=Sokoto VOR-DME (SOK) @ OurAirports|website=ourairports.com|access-date=2018-08-21}}</ref> The runway length does not include {{convert|118|m}} [[displaced threshold]]s on each end.
