'''{{nihongo|Matsudaira Chikayoshi|ÊùæÂπ≥ ËøëË™¨}};''' (January 10, 1829 &ndash; November 11, 1886) was a Japanese samurai of the late [[Edo period]] who served as daimy≈ç of the [[Funai Domain]] ([[Bungo Province]], 21,000 koku). Served in a variety of positions in the Tokugawa Shogunate, including that of [[wakadoshiyori]]. Resigning from the family headship in 1871, he went into retirement.

